From David Sternlight Subject Wiretapping reality today Some of the messages here seem to reflect the view that the government is listening in on everything and one will have to hide one's clipper messages somehow if non escrowed crypto goes A little perspective might be in The number of court ordered wire taps is pretty Law enforcement has to present pretty good evidence to get even that limited number of Thus the overwhelming majority of conversations are neither tapped nor recorded by the government and for that to happen they have to a Have a pretty good reason with evidence b Use this sparingly on highest priority pretty good Though the system may be imperfect it is a long way from the horror stories some here seem to believe or David Sternlight Great care has been taken to ensure the accuracy of our information errors and omissions